In RINS, the IMU can rotate continuously driven by motors so that the integral of bias tends to 0 in the same direction, and the influence of bias can be suppressed. The coordinate system used in this paper is described as follows.

The sensitive axis coordinate frame (s-frame) is obtained by making the three axes of IMU orthogonal after compensating the installation angles and scale coefficients of the three sensitive axes of IMU. The O - x s y s plane is a plane composed of sensitive axis of the X accelerometer and the Y accelerometer. The coordinate axis O - x s coincides with the sensitive axis of the X accelerometer and O - y s forms an acute angle with the sensitive axis of the Y accelerometer. Eventually, the O - x s , the O - y s and the O - z s form a right-hand coordinate system.

The body coordinate frame (b-frame) is a coordinate system fixed with the chassis. In this paper, it is selected as the right-front-upper coordinate system, in which the axis O - X b , O - Y b and O - Z b are the pitch axis, roll axis and azimuth axis respectively. The O - Y b coincides with the rotation axis of the outer frame. When the rotation angle of the outer frame is 0, the O - Z b coincides with the rotation axis of the inner frame. After compensating the installation deflection angle between the inner and outer frames, the coordinate transformation relationship between the b-frame and the s-frame can be expressed by the following directional cosine matrix C b s .

(1) C b s = cos η in cos η out sin η in - cos η in sin η out - sin η in cos η out cos η in sin η in sin η out sin η out 0 cos η out where η in is the rotation angle of the inner frame and η out is the rotation angle of the outer frame.

The navigation coordinate frame (n-frame) is defined as the east-north-up frame. It is used to describe the state of the carrier on the ground. The position information of the carrier, such as longitude, latitude and altitude, is described in the n-frame.
3. Anti-spoofing Kalman filter

When a spoofing signal intrudes into the GPS receiver, the navigation solution result of the receiver will deviate from the normal value, resulting in large positioning error or gradually deviate from the real value. The position of the carrier will be misled by the wrong navigation results. In the GPS/RINS integrated navigation system, the results of RINS are free from external interference and have sufficient accuracy in a short time. Therefore, the positioning value of GPS receiver can be judged by using the results of RINS and the priori results in the Kalman filter of the integration. Based on this, an anti-spoofing integrated navigation method is proposed in this paper.
3.1. Judge according to the trend error of INS

