Under normal conditions, the items in u k is normal distributed according to and the threshold T σ p can be determined according to the requirements of false alarm rate and inverse cumulative distribution function of normal distribution. A practical threshold selection method is to take the confidence range as E u k ± 3 σ p according to the 3 σ principle, that is, if the spoofing value f = 0 , u k should be within the range of interval - 3 σ p , 3 σ p according. On the contrary, if the difference u k is outside the judgment range, it can be deduced that f ≠ 0 , which means that the GPS positioning results at this time is not credible, and the GPS measurement value should be rejected for the integrated navigation.

Combining the above two strategies, we can effectively judge the reliability of GPS when the positioning results of GPS change suddenly or slowly. And the wrong positioning data can be eliminated when the GPS receiver is spoofed.
3.3. Process of the anti-spoofing Kalman filter

In the above judgment method, the solution results of inertial navigation and the time update results of KF are used. Therefore, the spoofing detection (SD) can be carried out between the time update and measurement update of KF, and the following anti-spoofing KF process can be designed Fig. 2 .

