In the KF process, the time update cycle is carried out according to and at the same frequency as the sampling frequency of IMU . After that, the GPS spoofing is checked by the SD module. When the GPS positioning result passes the detection, the measurement update cycle of the KF is carried out at a GPS frequency of 1 Hz. At t k + 1 , the state is updated as (23) X ̂ k + 1 = X ̂ k + 1 / k + K k + 1 Z k + 1 - H k + 1 X ̂ k + 1 / k where the K k + 1 is the filtering gain at the current time, which can be expressed as (24) K k + 1 = P k + 1 / k H k + 1 T H k + 1 P k + 1 / k H k + 1 T + R k + 1 - 1

At this time, the covariance matrix of the estimation error is (25) P k + 1 = I - K k + 1 H k + 1 P k + 1 / k I - K k + 1 H k + 1 T + R k + 1

When the GPS result is detected to be invalid at t k + 1 , the measurement update is no longer carried out to prevent the spoofing errors from affecting the integration result. At this time, the predicted values X ̂ k / k - 1 and P k / k - 1 in the time update are used instead of the measurement Z k + 1 for state estimation. The state is updated as (26) X ̂ k + 1 = ϕ k + 1 , k X ̂ k / k - 1 + K k Z k - H k X ̂ k / k - 1 and the covariance matrix is (27) P k + 1 = ϕ k + 1 , k I - K k H k P k / k - 1 ϕ k + 1 , k T + Q k

When a cycle of the KF update is completed, the error estimated by the KF is used to correct the inertial navigation result in an open loop, and the integration results with higher accuracy are output.
